<issue num="15" status="TC1">
<title>Locale::name requirement inconsistent</title>
<section><sref ref="[locale.members]"/></section>
<submitter>Nathan Myers</submitter>
<date>6 Aug 1998</date>

<discussion>
<p>locale::name() is described as returning a string that can be passed to a locale
constructor, but there is no matching constructor. </p>
</discussion>

<resolution>
<p>In <sref ref="[locale.members]"/>, paragraph 5, replace
&quot;<tt>locale(name())</tt>&quot; with
&quot;<tt>locale(name().c_str())</tt>&quot;.
</p>
</resolution>

</issue>
